    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in positioning measurement update handling\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning functionality was missing entirely from the codebase, causing a segmentation fault when the system attempted to call `free_positioning_measurement_update()` during positioning measurement update processing.\n\nThis fix implements the missing positioning functionality including proper memory management for positioning measurement updates.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: New file implementing positioning measurement update handling and memory management\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: New header file with function declarations\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_handlers.c`: Added positioning measurement update handler to the message processing matrix\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.h`: Included positioning header\n- `openair2/F1AP/CMakeLists.txt`: Added new positioning files to build configuration\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Configure the gNB with positioning capabilities enabled\n2. Send a PositioningMeasurementUpdate message from a connected UE\n3. Observe segmentation fault when the system attempts to free the positioning measurement update structure\n\nThe fix resolves this by providing a proper implementation of the missing functionality, preventing the crash and ensuring correct memory management.\n"
}